Russian scientist says the distant ancestor of humans had tentacles . 
  They lived more than 540 million years ago and used them for food . 
  It's likely they also had a complex nervous system like we do today . 
  Dr Elena Temereva studied the 'living fossil' Lingula anatina . 
  She says they likely had flexible appendages and a nervous system . 
  One theory suggests our ancestors were worm-like creatures . 
 